<h3>An early homepage alternative</h3>
<p>
  My original idea for DnsDigest was to have it scan DNS records for any domain name you entered. 
  I built this HTML-and-CSS only homepage as a postcard, where you could just type in your domain name and go. 
  I scratched this approach due to some technical limitations but thought it was fun to share.
</p>
<div class="figure-container">
  <figure>
    <%= image_tag "early-better-dns.png", alt: "A screenshot of an early version of the DNS digest homepage." %>
     <figcaption><span><strong>Postcard version:</strong> An early, quite different approach to the homepage. 
     This was done in HTML and CSS only, using radial and linear gradients to mimic a stamped ink effect.</span></figcaption>
  </figure>
</div>
<hr>
<h3>The Dashboard</h3>
<p>
  Inside the app, I wanted the first look of your DNS zone file to feel entirely different from 
  the laundry list you'd expect. Instead, I consolidated records together into more meaningful 
  groupings, which became the front doors to each of the more detailed sub-sections.
</p>
